<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">The channel math</h2></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">Why SMS wins specifically for gym leads</h2><ul class="ul"><li><strong>Decision urgency matches the channel.</strong> Someone inquiring about a gym is in active consideration. SMS matches their decision tempo; email does not.</li><li><strong>Conversational format works for prospect qualification.</strong> Gathering goals, schedule, location preferences happens naturally via text; awkwardly via email.</li><li><strong>Tour booking happens via reply.</strong> One text exchange to confirm tour time vs back-and-forth email scheduling.</li><li><strong>Mobile-native.</strong> Prospects researching gyms are on phones; SMS meets them there.</li><li><strong>Lower commitment to engage.</strong> Replying to a text feels lighter than replying to an email.</li></ul></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">Where email still wins</h2><ul class="ul"><li><strong>Receipts and confirmations.</strong> Long-form transactional content reads better in email.</li><li><strong>Billing communications.</strong> Members expect billing in email; SMS feels invasive for financial detail.</li><li><strong>Detailed content marketing.</strong> If the content is 500+ words, email is the format.</li><li><strong>Members who explicitly prefer email.</strong> Channel preference should be honored.</li><li><strong>Some compliance-sensitive communications.</strong> Specific legal/medical content with documentation requirements.</li></ul></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">Implementation: switching primary nurture channel</h2><ol class="ol"><li><strong>Audit current lead nurture flow.</strong> What touches happen in email today? Which would work better as SMS?</li><li><strong>Confirm consent capture flow.</strong> SMS marketing requires explicit consent in most jurisdictions; build into web form / Facebook Lead Form / paid ad form.</li><li><strong>Choose an SMS-native platform with conversation handling.</strong> Generic SMS broadcast tools won't deliver the conversational nurture experience. Purpose-built (<a href="https://fitagentic.ai" style="color:#00C853;">fitagentic.ai</a>) is built for this.</li><li><strong>Migrate the lead nurture sequence to SMS first.</strong> Keep email for receipts and billing.</li><li><strong>Measure: lead-to-tour conversion before vs after, opt-out rate, reply rate.</strong> Targets: 2x conversion lift; under 2% opt-out rate; 30%+ reply rate.</li></ol></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">Compliance basics</h2><ul class="ul"><li>Explicit consent at lead capture ("Yes, text me about classes and offers").</li><li>Opt-out instruction in first message of any new conversation.</li><li>Time-of-day restrictions (typically 8 AM - 9 PM local).</li><li>Brand identification in messages.</li><li>Documented consent records in CRM.</li></ul></div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">FAQ</h2>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">Will SMS feel intrusive to gym prospects?</h3><p class="faq-qa">Only if poorly executed. Relevant, conversational, low-pressure SMS feels like service. Generic broadcast feels intrusive. The format matters more than the channel.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">Is SMS marketing expensive?</h3><p class="faq-qa">Per-message costs are higher than email, but the dramatically higher conversion makes per-conversion cost lower. Cost economics favor SMS for gym lead nurture.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">Should we abandon email entirely?</h3><p class="faq-qa">No. Use both. SMS for lead nurture and time-sensitive moments; email for receipts, billing, long-form content.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">Does SMS work for older members?</h3><p class="faq-qa">Yes — open and reply rates are high across age groups in 2026. The channel-preference assumption that older members prefer email is largely outdated.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">How do we get consent without killing conversion?</h3><p class="faq-qa">Add a checkbox + clear language at lead form. Conversion impact is minimal. Quality of leads who consent is higher.</p></div>
</div></section>

